{"type":"message","id":"05ec3744","parentId":"50ff4abf","timestamp":"2026-04-18T15:15:45.958Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9ZKmPXDaLcq1vCbQprS5TL7D|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a0205d64819ab08ac8f965b94273","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"119:def as_records(df: pd.DataFrame) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n313:def sanitize_for_json(value: Any) -> Any:\n315:        return {k: sanitize_for_json(v) for k, v in value.items()}\n317:        return [sanitize_for_json(v) for v in value]\n319:        return [sanitize_for_json(v) for v in value]\n1134:    const allTrades = {json.dumps(as_records(all_trades_df), ensure_ascii=False)};\n1402:    metrics_file.write_text(json.dumps(sanitize_for_json(metrics_payload), ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"119:def as_records(df: pd.DataFrame) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n313:def sanitize_for_json(value: Any) -> Any:\n315:        return {k: sanitize_for_json(v) for k, v in value.items()}\n317:        return [sanitize_for_json(v) for v in value]\n319:        return [sanitize_for_json(v) for v in value]\n1134:    const allTrades = {json.dumps(as_records(all_trades_df), ensure_ascii=False)};\n1402:    metrics_file.write_text(json.dumps(sanitize_for_json(metrics_payload), ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776525345939}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4e0c10f","parentId":"05ec3744","timestamp":"2026-04-18T15:15:45.977Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_IVdDqyeU7HcrkkVX7C6lcEq9|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a0205d74819ab21d58774a2e71ef","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport html\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\nfrom paper_profile_utils import (  # type: ignore\n    journal_glob,\n    profile_name_from_config,\n    profile_slug_from_config,\n    report_path,\n)\n\ntry:\n    from run_live_execution_v1 import fetch_realtime_quote  # type: ignore\nexcept Exception:\n    def fetch_realtime_quote(ts_code: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        return {}\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDEFAULT_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json\"\nBENCHMARK_CANDIDATES = [\n    Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/index_000852_SH.csv\"),\n    PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"index_sh000852.csv\",\n]\n\n\ndef load_json(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n\n\ndef parse_float(value: Any, default: float = 0.0) -> float:\n    try:\n        return float(str(value).replace(\",\", \"\").strip())\n    except Exception:\n        return default\n\n\ndef parse_date_tag(value: Any) -> int:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip()\n    digits = re.sub(r\"\\D\", \"\", text)\n    if len(digits) >= 8:\n        return int(digits[:8])\n    return 0\n\n\ndef resolve_path(path_like: str) -> Path:\n    path = Path(str(path_like))\n    if path.is_absolute():\n        return path\n    return (PROJECT_ROOT / path).resolve()\n\n\ndef load_csv(path: Path) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return pd.DataFrame()\n    try:\n        return pd.read_csv(path)\n    except Exception:\n        return pd.DataFrame()\n\n\ndef safe_text_series(df: pd.DataFrame, column: str, default: str = \"\") -> pd.Series:\n    if column not in df.columns:\n        return pd.Series(default, index=df.index, dtype=object)\n    return df[column].fillna(default).astype(str)\n\n\ndef normalize_side(value: Any) -> str:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip().upper()\n    if text in {\"BUY\", \"SELL\"}:\n        return text\n    if any(token in text for token in [\"买\", \"B\"]):\n        return \"BUY\"\n    if any(token in text for token in [\"卖\", \"S\"]):\n        return \"SELL\"\n    return text\n\n\ndef derive_exit_metadata(\n    side: Any,\n    signal_reason: Any,\n    notes: Any = \"\",\n    exit_type: Any = \"\",\n    exit_reason: Any = \"\",\n) -> tuple[str, str]:\n    normalized_side = normalize_side(side)\n    signal_text = str(signal_reason or \"\").strip()\n    notes_text = str(notes or \"\").strip()\n    resolved_exit_type = str(exit_type or \"\").strip().lower()\n    resolved_exit_reason = str(exit_reason or \"\").strip()\n    if normalized_side != \"SELL\":\n        return resolved_exit_type, resolved_exit_reason\n\n    if not resolved_exit_reason:\n        resolved_exit_reason = signal_text or notes_text\n\n    if not resolved_exit_type:\n        match = re.search(r\"(?:^|[;\\s])exit_type=([^;\\s]+)\", notes_text, flags=re.IGNORECASE)\n        if match:\n            resolved_exit_type = str(match.group(1) or \"\").strip().lower()\n    if not resolved_exit_type and signal_text.lower().startswith(\"exit_engine:\"):\n        tail = signal_text.split(\":\", 1)[1].strip()\n        resolved_exit_type = tail.split(None, 1)[0].strip().lower() if tail else \"\"\n    if not resolved_exit_type and resolved_exit_reason:\n        resolved_exit_type = \"sell_signal\"\n    return resolved_exit_type, resolved_exit_reason\n\n\ndef as_records(df: pd.DataFrame) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    if df.empty:\n        return []\n    safe = df.where(pd.notna(df), None)\n    return safe.to_dict(orient=\"records\")\n\n\ndef clean_symbol_name(value: Any) -> str:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip()\n    return \"\" if text.lower() == \"nan\" else text\n\n\ndef load_symbol_name_map(symbols: set[str]) -> dict[str, str]:\n    mapping: dict[str, str] = {}\n    for symbol in sorted({str(x or \"\").strip().upper() for x in symbols if str(x or \"\").strip()}):\n        quote = fetch_realtime_quote(symbol)\n        name = clean_symbol_name(quote.get(\"name\", \"\"))\n        if name:\n            mapping[symbol] = name\n    return mapping\n\n\ndef attach_symbol_names(positions_df: pd.DataFrame, trades_df: pd.DataFrame) -> tuple[pd.DataFrame, pd.DataFrame]:\n    symbol_set: set[str] = set()\n    if not positions_df.empty:\n        symbol_set.update(str(x).strip().upper() for x in positions_df.get(\"symbol\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).fillna(\"\") if str(x).strip())\n    if not trades_df.empty:\n        symbol_set.update(str(x).strip().upper() for x in trades_df.get(\"ts_code\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).fillna(\"\") if str(x).strip())\n\n    name_map = load_symbol_name_map(symbol_set)\n\n    positions_out = positions_df.copy()\n    if not positions_out.empty:\n        positions_out[\"symbol_name\"] = safe_text_series(positions_out, \"name\").str.strip()\n        positions_out[\"symbol_name\"] = positions_out[\"symbol_name\"].mask(\n            positions_out[\"symbol_name\"].eq(\"\"),\n            safe_text_series(positions_out, \"symbol\").str.upper().map(name_map).fillna(\"\"),\n        )\n\n    trades_out = trades_df.copy()\n    if not trades_out.empty:\n        trades_out[\"symbol_name\"] = safe_text_series(trades_out, \"symbol_name\").str.strip()\n        trades_out[\"symbol_name\"] = trades_out[\"symbol_name\"].mask(\n            trades_out[\"symbol_name\"].eq(\"\"),\n            safe_text_series(trades_out, \"ts_code\").str.upper().map(name_map).fillna(\"\"),\n        )\n\n    return positions_out, trades_out\n\n\ndef symbol_cell_html(symbol: Any, symbol_name: Any) -> str:\n    symbol_text = html.escape(str(symbol or \"\"))\n    name_text = clean_symbol_name(symbol_name)\n    if not name_text:\n        return symbol_text\n    return (\n        f\"<div>{symbol_text}</div>\"\n        f\"<div class=\\\"symbol-name\\\">{html.escape(name_text)}</div>\"\n    )\n\n\ndef fmt(value: Any, digits: int = 2, suffix: str = \"\") -> str:\n\n[1247 more lines in file. Use offset=181 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776525345958}}
{"type":"message","id":"14a79fb3","parentId":"a4e0c10f","timestamp":"2026-04-18T15:16:17.479Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing data handling**\n\nI'm thinking about how `as_records` utilizes `df.where`, and whether None can convert numeric values to NaN. Actually, using `where(pd.notna(df), None)` for float columns keeps NaN due to the float dtype not accepting None. Then, I note that `json.dumps` with NaN set to allow_nan true outputs NaN, which is valid in JavaScript but not in strict JSON. I should dig deeper into the recent UI, as a blank layer suggests issues, possibly with the journal file or filters. Inspecting the latest dashboard might help figure out if `allTrades` is empty despite the journal existing.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a029cf7c819aabb732a699534b45\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp46AxFrh1Rcx68c3ijOlZ0oLt8bmHfo28u-kLoM3FIZBd4hyGrZQM2aK-CL5uPz4r7yr2N9jGB7bpq1zOUQ_z78VD2uRW0C7-aes9B8A8Z_uz5Osx0nHiTGO_A9XrBmadY7NDyhUNrhenPqpjqCkAOECXZ1J6YznPEcX-J9nNlqUOB1LRC1ME_1zvwq6a1Dx_us_yzohp9XHFqZqvhUrDAwRAz0JiKznCyWdjIc2gQ3xQjKSwfvqIEl2LSjkq5tQNCMLlVwZ0-b4jiOgKnQEwmrRLD5S7nqDiTgyjoZ4sZXGE4-1A2ysLOlhz9UmPQk9PITmXMWHstVu7ff0PTvHNddZPKpLwDQDr5H6KWt2JQG8BAxvYXqAdUsKX55jXpZ202x25uvUFNWqTZn2dRG2mvTBNm9IXbK-qPxX3FxY4h6xzFe9zU4LwqFeaE2PP0LhndJogxzsGnMHzORnL1bSia-cDp8cbDGGoHEvnmo0vzC-0vQ_0Jx668zkYqKSp_Rrub0mXI-VxRZS3gng8sn_VV5jVOlLaXVHLjt0fIBimpKbzfTizqQYbcAvV97yWqsDemXM1vPD6eAaM1BpTympNtGqUXEUwsbOLw0fZ1Yd2T6E8a1i-MczS1rx3WFAdWrFiJjZW55g5So-UIZd2GzLT8EY8nEyqhspkRn6-MOxe5QuFWzQwAaIMWdyiLt3kQAxUs5n56dmYBWVSFWZTNlzYYkb7EJIkCLrngjnMCx46IRCl4uCngWGWmUTp6SjOT_GadYeQk36PS-eJvyIbEwERgZx-YlE9Gqt-moGG5YbPro_i_9ykvX2awo5V7gMk1qvOO3LyPh-X9aH7kCVdp4bAltSuPXzQok-9nSR1WGrwTx70JzS0O0EN8j_y3K8CTXWoWE7qBm2e8PEd_sIYfWkDoSIOrzFmZLdw3bihc3w-zk9SVgDbkaMN_Jcr3mx5Qno2MpAnVE8xsAsLBhXFP2N6bVeHk3Dk-Xw_svp9p3WbwBwzRG23TSYBFPghWAEbluSZx3p914Fx5PcijufudnPqTTCOHnS4GYg3ViQJlqIpam1pLMTbhFKXrS_6JP