ify the script to pre-render rows from `all_trades_df` to address the issue effectively.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Fixing empty table issues**\\n\\nI need to verify if the current `<tbody>` is empty, and it turns out it is until the JavaScript runs. If there's a JavaScript failure, the user would just see a blank table. To address this, I'm thinking about implementing server-side fallback rows. It makes sense to include a fallback even if there are no trades. I could also enhance the script to ensure it’s robust against Plotly errors, but since `tradeTable` render is called before Plotly, any parsing failures wouldn’t result in a blank table. I might need to add a helper function for rendering trade rows in HTML.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"我找到一个很像根因的点：成交/日志区的 `<tbody>` 初始是空的，完全依赖前端 JS 再填。  \n只要脚本有一点报错或没执行，这一层就直接是空白。  \n我先把它改成**服务端先渲染一版兜底**，这样就算 JS 翻车，日志层也不会空。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a06d0148819ab7f01670ca4ee3fa\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9wS4nxWgusrhoBelbAoZB34a|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a06f15a0819a9887a2d91446ff00","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def positions_rows_html\\|def metric_rows_html\\|rows_html\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent","timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"grep -n \\\"def positions_rows_html\\\\|def metric_rows_html\\\\|rows_html\\\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent\",\"timeout\":30}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6kd6cpzfyomEN7JqhET6QT6B|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a06f15ac819aa430a78440c4ca82","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_paper_trading_da