pect things nearby after checking out the `trade_filter_options`. There seems to be more helpers I could potentially make, so I'm curious about how I should structure this. I want to make sure everything flows well together. Alright, let's get started on this to see what I can come up with!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ImCB2ZKIirR5M4IGQQwqVbdB|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a083b56c819ab1c5975cbe097067","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py","offset":780,"limit":80},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py\",\"offset\":780,\"limit\":80}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"beecode","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":130881,"output":79,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133520,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776525436271,"responseId":"resp_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a07e5e90819a9526aa0e95df7a0d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e1710b9","parentId":"6ec930c6","timestamp":"2026-04-18T15:17:25.780Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ImCB2ZKIirR5M4IGQQwqVbdB|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a083b56c819ab1c5975cbe097067","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\ndef trade_exit_type_options(trades: pd.DataFrame) -> str:\n    if trades.empty:\n        return \"\"\n    exit_types = sorted({str(x).strip().lower() for x in trades.get(\"exit_type\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).fillna(\"\") if str(x).strip()})\n    return \"\\n\".join(\n        [\n            f\"<option value=\\\"{html.escape(exit_type)}\\\">{html.escape(exit_type)}</option>\"\n            for exit_type in exit_types\n        ]\n    )\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"生成模拟盘观察面板\")\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--config\",\n        default=str(DEFAULT_CONFIG_PATH),\n        help=\"模拟盘配置文件；默认使用 aggressive profile\",\n    )\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    cfg = load_json(resolve_path(args.config))\n    profile_slug = profile_slug_from_config(cfg)\n    profile_name = profile_name_from_config(cfg)\n    account_file = resolve_path(\n        str(\n            cfg.get(\n                \"account_latest_file\",\n                report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"account_latest\", profile_slug=profile_slug).relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT),\n            )\n        )\n    )\n    positions_file = resolve_path(\n        str(\n            cfg.get(\n                \"positions_latest_file\",\n                report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"positions_latest\", profile_slug=profile_slug).relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT),\n            )\n        )\n    )\n    curve_file = resolve_path(\n        str(\n            cfg.get(\n                \"nav_curve_file\",\n                report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"nav_curve\", profile_slug=profile_slug).relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT),\n            )\n        )\n    )\n\n    if not account_file.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"未找到模拟盘账户快照: {account_file}\")\n\n    account = load_json(account_file)\n    initial_cash = parse_float(account.get(\"initial_cash\"), 0.0)\n    journal_file = (\n        resolve_path(str((account.get(\"files\") or {}).get(\"today_journal\", \"\")))\n        if account.get(\"files\")\n        else report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"journal\", profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=str(account.get(\"date_tag\", \"\")))\n    )\n    positions_df = load_csv(positions_file)\n    curve_df = load_csv(curve_file)\n    today_trades_df = load_csv(journal_file)\n    all_trades_df = load_all_trade_rows(REPORT_DIR, profile_slug=profile_slug)\n    positions_df, all_trades_df = attach_symbol_names(positions_df, all_trades_df)\n    benchmark_df, benchmark_name, benchmark_path = load_benchmark_frame(cfg)\n    benchmark_latest_date = (\n        pd.to_datetime(benchmark_df[\"date\"], errors=\"coerce\").dropna().max().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n        if not benchmark_df.empty\n        else \"\"\n    )\n    perf_df = prepare_performance_frame(curve_df, benchmark_df, initial_cash=initial_cash)\n    trade_stats = compute_trade_statistics(all_trades_df)\n    metrics = compute_performance_metrics(perf_df, trade_stats, benchmark_name)\n\n    date_tag = str(account.get(\"date_tag\") or extract_date_tag(account_file))\n    now_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\n\n    if not today_trades_df.empty:\n\n[568 more lines in file. Use offset=860 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776525445762}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f9c0799","parentId":"3e1710b9","timestamp":"2026-04-18T15:17:43.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Sanitizing trade payloads**\n\nI’m thinking about adding a helper and possibly sanitizing the trade payload to avoid NaN issues. While JavaScript handles NaN, we should sanitize before using `json.dumps` for allTrades, perfRows, and positionRows to replace NaN with null, especially for environments that might not accept it. Since Infinity could also cause problems, better to use the existing `sanitize_for_json`. After that, consts like allTrades will have nulls, plus a server-side fallback seems like a solid approach. I'll consider rendering the allTrades table initially from all_trades_df with minimal changes.\n\n**Inspecting dashboard generation**\n\nI need to take a look at the latest dashboard generation command to determine if I should rerun it for one profile, or potentially all profiles. It might be that only the aggressive profile is affected, but the user could prefer something more generic for the log layer across all dashboards. If the script is common, a patch could fix everything. It seems like I could regenerate the aggressive dashboard for testing or even the latest versions of all profiles. I just need to inspect the config files to be sure.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3a08d76f4819ab4dae5c63c39a1cd\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp46CVARqavwJGEECHQCcaXuUSHf3DluaSe0-atSRBtnfMC08Y7gsm10IQI4flGsPYMexCgHo6tIsOvBBXzjHRvJO1cO3EIaBNDc7OIxf1dkcPVDjAvt0-6Ps4zkZ-9iriVPQI-n5G44F5IBm9P59IUirz66VZ-Vi1hp33KNyN8RnxebZ4f76R6mGQiONfJzlvAW31VD8TJPZ6WwsL4GB8NfKtsgdqRe43zKHNNcgd4L6NK4b8SJLism_vyKw8sFvL2Z-hyzGfkqbWCWrfefbDgp7lp6OQMnmdGeGai5WMW6CSgzZkuAom74nBz32t7wClkU6ePporNtyCSonu6jujbvG_SdkCPwhU5qthofnvNfKLqvTrW1PF-AKfX3N2sbbH7wpFKIdYHWwAWAt23-Gxpen-1wZdGTK_XvrO0Dy_YmRMjJnnE5P_d2SCMdV6AcBKQ_B9B3Azbzh2buTf2jpOOZcvUM4_dqPY6WJyoNIveXLKvQDuVq5lKkrHNnXE4Zqk