JriJaZlKp7lMkjD3CZzjjAF0K9EMOcAwmrnFmyscFImCINPNlmnJBmpYG5ZtqfEXEH36TYIDEA9mXc-YkMKFj8_sx8linHVrLFH0PqJdbjWDsfX5-syTTYf6pIEPo-QCjTRdSJpNqfMnsYknAbobIUFm-ErfeXhni9Wo0I-iw4NnuMi53koERpw-Vjlddd8LKfirPy2_3IKG6AeQURi-MMhR1kXPSJQjY9sL2IXnfgY--g7cFvUzHmejlqtPACj-OH7JXLwebWIEl70VCoHzhBk0qlvFnHfkN-hn_6SBxjO9CeVeoLGdoqZc4ohJ0svCPUmxrTZHj0NM=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering data issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to patch the enrich script to use the PriceFetcher multi-source. There's also the idea of patching run_daily_overlays to utilize the latest positions file if today’s is missing. The user seems upset by the analysis based on stale data; fixing this should directly address their concern. I might inspect the enrich_holdings_with_prices issue because it only uses Tencent and could be returning previous close prices instead of the latest ones. The user's complaint centers around our direct analysis utilizing a_stock_history file, even though overlays use enriched prices. Moving forward, we might want to add a quick quote helper or update the MEMORY/TOOLS, plus create a reusable CLI script for better data handling.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing lag issues**\\n\\nI can't change the overall system but can consider updating the workspace note, possibly regarding AGENTS. I probably need to run a script to enrich today's holdings using a multi-source approach to generate the selected_real_positions_latest_enriched.csv. The user's immediate concern isn't specific to a stock but is about solving the lag. I could summarize the fix and mention that the memory_search isn't available. After making edits, I’ll need to commit. I'll patch enrich_holdings_with_prices.py to import PriceFetcher and robustly fetch prices per ticker, including price_source, timestamp, and a staleness flag. Using Tushare for the latest daily close seems viable since the user’s price of 105.44 likely reflects a recent close.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating for price fetching**\\n\\nIt looks like PriceFetcher already handles this. I need to ensure that when it's after hours and Tencent data isn't available, Tushare daily can provide the expected figure of 105.44. That sounds promising! I think I should patch the script to read from the existing latest enriched data. I'll go ahead and edit the necessary parts to improve the functionality. Let’s make these updates to ensure everything works smoothly!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"我直接把持仓补价脚本改成“多源 + 时间戳 + 新鲜度标记”，以后不会再默默把旧价当最新。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3b172a1c8819aaff74cc26f6504ea\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_xxzzk5ZKbLWEn0XPBNSk7FkD|fc_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3b172b8c8819a8ed9a97d5d34f59a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py","edits":[{"oldText":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices from Tencent Finance API.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\n\nFetches previous trading day's close price for each ticker via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn API,\nthen computes unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport sys\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nimport ssl\nimport certifi\nfrom pathlib import Path\n","newText":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Enrich holdings CSV with freshest available prices.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\n\nPrice policy:\n- Prefer freshest available multi-source quote\n- Persist source/timestamp/staleness instead of silently pretending old prices are current\n- Compute unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport sys\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nimport ssl\nimport certifi\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom price_fetcher_with_fallback import PriceFetcher  # type: ignore\n"},{"oldText":"def main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--input\", \"-i\", required=True, help=\"Input holdings CSV\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--output\", \"-o\", required=True, help=\"Output enriched CSV\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Input file not found: {input_path}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 1\n\n    # Read holdings\n    holdings: list[dict] = []\n    with input_path.open(newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\n        holdings = list(reader)\n\n    tickers = [h[\"symbol\"] for h in holdings]\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Fetching prices for {len(tickers)} tickers...\")\n\n    price_map = fetch_prices(tickers)\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Got prices for {len(price_map)} tickers\")\n\n    # Enrich holdings\n    enriched: list[dict] = []\n    for h in holdings:\n        h = dict(h)\n        symbol = h[\"symbol\"]\n        cost_str = h.get(\"cost_price\", \"0\")\n        try:\n            cost = float(cost_str)\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\n            cost = 0.0\n\n        # Find price\n        current_price = None\n        prev_close = None\n        change_pct = None\n\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\n            if symbol.endswith(suffix):\n                qt_key = prefix + symbol.replace(suffix, \"\")\n                if qt_key in price_map:\n                    p = price_map[qt_key]\n                    current_price = p[\"current_price\"]\n                    prev_close = p[\"prev_close\"]\n                    change_pct = p[\"change_pct\"]\n                break\n\n        h[\"current_price\"] = str(current_price) if current_price is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"prev_close\"] = str(prev_close) if prev_close is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"change_pct_today\"] = str(change_pct) if change_pct is not None else \"\"\n\n        if current_price and cost and cost > 0:\n            pnl_pct = (current_price - cost) / cost * 100\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = f\"{pnl_pct:.2f}\"\n            mkt_val = current_price * float(h.get(\"quantity\", 0))\n            h[\"market_value\"] = f\"{mkt_val:.2f}\"\n        else:\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = \"\"\n            h[\"market_value\"] = \"\"\n\n        enriched.append(h)\n","newText":"def main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Enrich holdings CSV with freshest available prices\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--input\", \"-i\", required=True, help=\"Input holdings CSV\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--output\", \"-o\", required=True, help=\"Output enriched CSV\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Input file not found: {input_path}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 1\n\n    # Read holdings\n    holdings: list[dict] = []\n    with input_path.open(newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\n        holdings = list(reader)\n\n    tickers = [h[\"symbol\"] for h in holdings]\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Fetching freshest prices for {len(tickers)} tickers...\")\n\n    # Batch Tencent first (fast); fall back per-symbol to multi-source fetcher.\n    tencent_map = fetch_prices(tickers)\n    fetcher = PriceFetcher()\n    now_iso = datetime.now().isoformat()\n\n    # Enrich holdings\n    enriched: list[dict] = []\n    for h in holdings:\n        h = dict(h)\n        symbol = h[\"symbol\"]\n        cost_str = h.get(\"cost_price\", \"0\")\n        try:\n            cost = float(cost_str)\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\n            cost = 0.0\n\n        current_price = None\n        prev_close = None\n        change_pct = None\n        price_source = \"\"\n        price_timestamp = \"\"\n        price_is_stale = \"\"\n        price_error = \"\"\n\n        # 1) fast Tencent batch result\n        quote_found = False\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\n            if symbol.endswith(suffix):\n                qt_key = prefix + symbol.replace(suffix, \"\")\n                if qt_key in tencent_map:\n                    p = tencent_map[qt_key]\n                    current_price = p[\"current_price\"]\n                    prev_close = p[\"prev_close\"]\n                    change_pct = p[\"change_pct\"]\n                    if current_price is not None and float(current_price) > 0:\n                        price_source = \"tencent_batch\"\n                        price_timestamp = p.get(\"date\") or now_iso\n                        price_is_stale = \"0\"\n                        quote_found = True\n                break\n\n        # 2) multi-source fallback if batch quote failed\n        if not quote_found:\n            result = fetcher.fetch_price(symbol)\n            if result.success and result.price > 0:\n                current_price = result.price\n                price_source = result.source\n                price_timestamp = result.timestamp or now_iso\n                # Non-intraday sources may still be latest close rather than live quote; mark explicitly.\n                price_is_stale = \"1\" if result.source in {\"tushare\", \"yahoo\"} else \"0\"\n                price_error = \"\"\n            else:\n                price_source = result.source or \"all_failed\"\n                price_timestamp = result.timestamp or now_iso\n                price_is_stale = \"1\"\n                price_error = result.error or \"fetch_failed\"\n\n        h[\"current_price\"] = str(current_price) if current_price is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"prev_close\"] = str(prev_close) if prev_close is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"change_pct_today\"] = str(change_pct) if change_pct is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"price_source\"] = price_source\n        h[\"price_timestamp\"] = price_timestamp\n        h[\"price_is_stale\"] = price_is_stale\n        h[\"price_error\"] = price_error\n\n        if current_price and cost and cost > 0:\n            pnl_pct = (float(current_price) - cost) / cost * 100\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = f\"{pnl_pct:.2f}\"\n            mkt_val = float(current_price) * float(h.get(\"quantity\", 0))\n            h[\"market_value\"] = f\"{mkt_val:.2f}\"\n        else:\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = \"\"\n            h[\"market_value\"] = \"\"\n\n        enriched.append(h)\n"},{"oldText":"    print(\"\\n=== Price Summary ===\")\n    for h in enriched:\n        pnl = h.get(\"unrealized_pnl_pct\", \"N/A\")\n        cur = h.get(\"current_price\", \"N/A\")\n        chg = h.get(\"change_pct_today\", \"\")\n        chg_str = f\"{float(chg):+.2f}%\" if chg else \"\"\n        print(f\"  {h['symbol']:15s} {h.get('name',''):10s}  cur={cur:>8s}  cost={h.get('cost_price',''):>8s}  pnl={pnl:>8s}%  today={chg_str}\")\n    return 0\n","newText":"    print(\"\\n=== Price Summary ===\")\n    for h in enriched:\n        pnl = h.get(\"unrealized_pnl_pct\", \"N/A\")\n        cur = h.get(\"current_price\", \"N/A\")\n        chg = h.get(\"change_pct_today\", \"\")\n        chg_str = f\"{float(chg):+.2f}%\" if chg else \"\"\n        stale = \"STALE\" if str(h.get(\"price_is_stale\", \"0\")) == \"1\" else \"FRESH\"\n        source = h.get(\"price_source\", \"\")\n        print(\n            f\"  {h['symbol']:15s} {h.get('name',''):10s}  cur={cur:>8s}  cost={h.get('cost_price',''):>8s}  \"\n            f\"pnl={pnl:>8s}%  today={chg_str:<8s}  source={source:<12s}  {stale}\"\n        )\n    return 0\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices from Tencent Finance API.\\n\\nUsage:\\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\\\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\\\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\\n\\nFetches previous trading day's close price for each ticker via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn API,\\nthen computes unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nfrom __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport argparse\\nimport csv\\nimport sys\\nimport urllib.request\\nimport urllib.error\\nimport ssl\\nimport certifi\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\",\"newText\":\"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"Enrich holdings CSV with freshest available prices.\\n\\nUsage:\\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\\\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\\\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\\n\\nPrice policy:\\n- Prefer freshest available multi-source quote\\n- Persist source/timestamp/staleness instead of silently pretending old prices are current\\n- Compute unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nfrom __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport argparse\\nimport csv\\nimport sys\\nimport urllib.request\\nimport urllib.error\\nimport ssl\\nimport certifi\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\nfrom price_fetcher_with_fallback import PriceFetcher  # type: ignore\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"def main() -> int:\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\\\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices\\\")\\n    parser.add_argument(\\\"--input\\\", \\\"-i\\\", required=True, help=\\\"Input holdings CSV\\\")\\n    parser.add_argument(\\\"--output\\\", \\\"-o\\\", required=True, help=\\\"Output enriched CSV\\\")\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\\n    if not input_path.exists():\\n        print(f\\\"[enrich_holdings] Input file not found: {input_path}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n        return 1\\n\\n    # Read holdings\\n    holdings: list[dict] = []\\n    with input_path.open(newline=\\\"\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\") as f:\\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\\n        holdings = list(reader)\\n\\n    tickers = [h[\\\"symbol\\\"] for h in holdings]\\n    print(f\\\"[enrich_holdings] Fetching prices for {len(tickers)} tickers...\\\")\\n\\n    price_map = fetch_prices(tickers)\\n    print(f\\\"[enrich_holdings] Got prices for {len(price_map)} tickers\\\")\\n\\n    # Enrich holdings\\n    enriched: list[dict] = []\\n    for h in holdings:\\n        h = dict(h)\\n        symbol = h[\\\"symbol\\\"]\\n        cost_str = h.get(\\\"cost_price\\\", \\\"0\\\")\\n        try:\\n            cost = float(cost_str)\\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\\n            cost = 0.0\\n\\n        # Find price\\n        current_price = None\\n        prev_close = None\\n        change_pct = None\\n\\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\\n            if symbol.endswith(suffix):\\n                qt_key = prefix + symbol.replace(suffix, \\\"\\\")\\n                if qt_key in price_map:\\n                    p = price_map[qt_key]\\n                    current_price = p[\\\"current_price\\\"]\\n                    prev_close = p[\\\"prev_close\\\"]\\n                    change_pct = p[\\\"change_pct\\\"]\\n                break\\n\\n        h[\\\"current_price\\\"] = str(current_price) if current_price is not None else \\\"\\\"\\n        h[\\\"prev_close\\\"] = str(prev_close) if prev_close is not None else \\\"\\\"\\n        h[\\\"change_pct_today\\\"] = str(change_pct) if change_pct is not None else \\\"\\\"\\n\\n        if current_price and cost and cost > 0:\\n            pnl_pct = (current_price - cost) / cost * 100\\n            h[\\\"unrealized_pnl_pct\\\"] = f\\\"{pnl_pct:.2f}\\\"\\n            mkt_val = current_price * float(h.get(\\\"quantity\\\", 0))\\n            h[\\\"market_value\\\"] = f\\\"{mkt_val:.2f}\\\"\\n        else:\\n            h[\\\"unrealized_pnl_pct\\\"] = \\\"\\\"\\n            h[\\\"market_value\\\"] = \\\"\\\"\\n\\n        enriched.append(h)\\n\",\"newText\":\"def main() -> int:\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\\\"Enrich holdings CSV with freshest available prices\\\")\\n    parser.add_argument(\\\"--input\\\", \\\"-i\\\", required=True, help=\\\"Input holdings CSV\\\")\\n    parser.add_argument(\\\"--output\\\", \\\"-o\\\", required=True, help=\\\"Output enriched CSV\\\")\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\\n    if not input_path.exists():\\n        print(f\\\"[enrich_holdings] Input file not found: {input_path}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n        return 1\\n\\n    # Read holdings\\n    holdings: list[dict] = []\\n    with input_path.open(newline=\\\"\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\") as f:\\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\\n        holdings = list(reader)\\n\\n    tickers = [h[\\\"symbol\\\"] for h in holdings]\\n    print(f\\\"[enrich_holdings] Fetching freshest prices for {len(tickers)} tickers...\\\")\\n\\n    # Batch Tencent first (fast); fall back per-symbol to multi-source fetcher.\\n    tencent_map = fetch_prices(tickers)\\n    fetcher = PriceFetcher()\\n    now_iso = datetime.now().isoformat()\\n\\n    # Enrich holdings\\n    enriched: list[dict] = []\\n    for h in holdings:\\n        h = dict(h)\\n        symbol = h[\\\"symbol\\\"]\\n        cost_str = h.get(\\\"cost_price\\\", \\\"0\\\")\\n        try:\\n            cost = float(cost_str)\\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\\n            cost = 0.0\\n\\n        current_price = None\\n        prev_close = None\\n        change_pct = None\\n        price_source = \\\"\\\"\\n        price_timestamp = \\\"\\\"\\n        price_is_stale = \\\"\\\"\\n        price_error = \\\"\\\"\\n\\n        # 1) fast Tencent batch result\\n        quote_found = False\\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\\n            if symbol.endswith(suffix):\\n                qt_key = prefix + symbol.replace(suffix, \\\"\\\")\\n                if qt_key in tencent_map:\\n                    p = tencent_map[qt_key]\\n                    current_price = p[\\\"current_price\\\"]\\n                    prev_close = p[\\\"prev_close\\\"]\\n                    change_pct = p[\\\"change_pct\\\"]\\n                    if current_price is not None and float(current_price) > 0:\\n                        price_source = \\\"tencent_batch\\\"\\n                        price_timestamp = p.get(\\\"date\\\") or now_iso\\n                        price_is_stale = \\\"0\\\"\\n                        quote_found = True\\n                break\\n\\n        # 2) multi-source fallback if batch quote failed\\n        if not quote_found:\\n            result = fetcher.fetch_price(symbol)\\n            if result.success and result.price > 0:\\n                current_price = result.price\\n                price_source = result.source\\n                price_timestamp = result.timestamp or now_iso\\n                # Non-intraday sources may still be latest close rather than live quote; mark explicitly.\\n                price_is_stale = \\\"1\\\" if result.source in {\\\"tushare\\\", \\\"yahoo\\\"} else \\\"0\\\"\\n                price_error = \\\"\\\"\\n            else:\\n                price_source = result.source or \\\"all_failed\\\"\\n                price_timestamp = result.timestamp or now_iso\\n                price_is_stale = \\\"1\\\"\\n                price_error = result.error or \\\"fetch_failed\\\"\\n\\n        h[\\\"current_price\\\"] = str(current_price) if current_price is not None else \\\"\\\"\\n        h[\\\"prev_close\\\"] = str(prev_close) if prev_close is not None else \\\"\\\"\\n        h[\\\"change_pct_today\\\"] = str(change_pct) if change_pct is not None else \\\"\\\"\\n        h[\\\"price_source\\\"] = price_source\\n        h[\\\"price_timestamp\\\"] = price_timestamp\\n        h[\\\"price_is_stale\\\"] = price_is_stale\\n        h[\\\"price_error\\\"] = price_error\\n\\n        if current_price and cost and cost > 0:\\n            pnl_pct = (float(current_price) - cost) / cost * 100\\n            h[\\\"unrealized_pnl_pct\\\"] = f\\\"{pnl_pct:.2f}\\\"\\n            mkt_val = float(current_price) * float(h.get(\\\"quantity\\\", 0))\\n            h[\\\"market_value\\\"] = f\\\"{mkt_val:.2f}\\\"\\n        else:\\n            h[\\\"unrealized_pnl_pct\\\"] = \\\"\\\"\\n            h[\\\"market_value\\\"] = \\\"\\\"\\n\\n        enriched.append(h)\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"    print(\\\"\\\\n=== Price Summary ===\\\")\\n    for h in enriched:\\n        pnl = h.get(\\\"unrealized_pnl_pct\\\", \\\"N/A\\\")\\n        cur = h.get(\\\"current_price\\\", \\\"N/A\\\")\\n        chg = h.get(\\\"change_pct_today\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        chg_str = f\\\"{float(chg):+.2f}%\\\" if chg else \\\"\\\"\\n        print(f\\\"  {h['symbol']:15s} {h.get('name',''):10s}  cur={cur:>8s}  cost={h.get('cost_price',''):>8s}  pnl={pnl:>8s}%  today={chg_str}\\\")\\n    return 0\\n\",\"newText\":\"    print(\\\"\\\\n=== Price Summary ===\\\")\\n    for h in enriched:\\n        pnl = h.get(\\\"unrealized_pnl_pct\\\", \\\"N/A\\\")\\n        cur = h.get(\\\"current_price\\\", \\\"N/A\\\")\\n        chg = h.get(\\\"change_pct_today\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        chg_str = f\\\"{float(chg):+.2f}%\\\" if chg else \\\"\\\"\\n        stale = \\\"STALE\\\" if str(h.get(\\\"price_is_stale\\\", \\\"0\\\")) == \\\"1\\\" else \\\"FRESH\\\"\\n        source = h.get(\\\"price_source\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        print(\\n            f\\\"  {h['symbol']:15s} {h.get('name',''):10s}  cur={cur:>8s}  cost={h.get('cost_price',''):>8s}  \\\"\\n            f\\\"pnl={pnl:>8s}%  today={chg_str:<8s}  source={source:<12s}  {stale}\\\"\\n        )\\n    return 0\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"beecode","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":271176,"output":3015,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":274191,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776529761815,"responseId":"resp_0fad9e409c19087f0169e3b1643010819a8cdd46bfc4763f33"}}
